Job Responsibilities:

1. Responsible for the structural design of related products to ensure their safety, reliability, and efficiency;

2. Collaborate with project managers and other engineers to ensure the project is completed on time and meets expected goals;

3. Analyze the design data of the product, develop corresponding manufacturing processes, and optimize the processes;

4. Guide and supervise technical workers in the product manufacturing process to ensure product quality and production efficiency;

5. Participate in product design review and evaluation and provide improvement suggestions.

6. Follow up on the progress of product development and trial production processes;

7. Produce samples and conduct testing according to customer and new product requirements;

8. Develop a testing plan, BOM, and determine product specifications;

9. Resolve engineering and technical issues that arise during trial production and production of products;

10. Participate in project requirement analysis, discussion and provide technical support;

11. Assist superiors in completing project plans and summarizing and reviewing project results;

12. Research the existing electronic control system and propose improvement plans;

13. Responsible for the development and follow-up of new products;

14. Responsible for following up and handling various issues related to the old products;

15. Responsible for the production, testing, and modification of samples;

16. Responsible for handling issues related to product trial production and mass production, as well as following up on product design progress;

17. Responsible for the preparation and modification of temporary product lists and parts lists.

Qualifications:

1. Bachelor's degree or above, majoring in mechanical, engineering, electronics, electromechanical engineering, etc.

2. More than 2 years of work experience in the small household appliance industry, such as humidifiers, air purifiers, groomers, and trimmers, with extensive experience in product design;

3. Familiar with commonly used structural design software, such as AutoCAD, SolidWorks/pro, etc;

4. Good analytical, problem-solving, communication, team spirit, and coordination skills.

5. Have a solid foundation in electronic disciplines such as C/C++, analog circuits, digital circuits, and circuit analysis;

6. Familiar with microcontroller cores and hardware frameworks, proficient in STM32 series microcontrollers and ARM architecture chip programming;

7. Be capable of designing and developing hardware, including completing schematics and PCB designs.

Job Type: Full-time

Pay: From Rp2,000.00 per month

Language:

* Mandarin (Required)

Job Description
Responsibilities:* Functionally report to a senior engineer appointed by Department Head;
* Assume the role as a shift geotechnical engineer and assist Lead Geotechnical Engineer and/or Offshore Manager with various tasks during fieldwork (on domestic and overseas offshore assignments);
* Perform sample logging and soil classification, and input of data into various geotechnical software packages;
* Process in situ test data and perform offshore laboratory works;
* Generate field deliverables including geotechnical logs;
* Assist in planning and coordinating field investigations;
* Assign laboratory tests and monitor progress through the laboratory;
* Maintain clear and organised records of test data;
* Collect the field operations data from various departments for field reporting purpose;
* Evaluate field and laboratory test data, and develop foundation soil parameters;
* Produce reports for final review by senior staff;
* Perform technical assignments with supervision;
* Assist other professionals with technical training, proposals, invoices and marketing;
* Assist senior engineers in related project administrative tasks;
* Perform other engineering related tasks as and when required;
* Contribute to continuous improvement initiatives by providing feedback on offshore laboratory workflows;
* Full compliance with Fugro and Client QHSSE requirements.


Requirement:* Degree in Civil Engineering or related discipline or equivalent in education and experience;
* Ability and availability to be on offshore assignments (domestic and overseas) for 180 days or more per year, on rotation basis. The total stated offshore days per year is non guarantee and may change at any time subject to company’s business needs;
* Has proven offshore and onshore experience (3 years min) in geotechnical engineering environment, preferably in support of the marine oil & gas, offshore wind farm projects;
* Report writing skills are necessary, and some ability with data processing would be preferred;
* Strong ability in verbal and written English (technical) language is essential;
* Has good teamwork, adaptability, and communication skills.


Disclaimer for recruitment agencies:
Fugro does not accept any unsolicited applications from recruitment agencies. Acquisition to Fugro Recruitment or any Fugro employee is not appreciated.

Construction Management Engineer


**Country:** Indonesia
**Position Location:** Belitang, Ogan Komering Ulu Timur, South Sumatra,
**Contract Type:** Contract
**Work Pattern:** Full Time
**Sector:** International Development
**Discipline:** International development
**Job Ref:** 3669
