**Job Description:**
* To carry out overall management and coordination for the construction management and supervision team of the consultant in cooperation with Team Leader;
* To review the existing reports, design documents and design drawings for overall irrigation facilities to be newly constructed or improved;
* To check the control points and bench marks used for previous surveying and, if needed to evaluate the accuracy of existing topographic maps for design adjustment;
* To make sure to review and revise existing design documents, calculation and drawings and propose to adjust the design when necessary;
* To execute the construction supervision of civil works of main system of Lempuing Irrigation Scheme including the following items:
	+ To assist the Employer/ the Engineer to confirm and mutually agree on the work responsibility, method of supervision, document/letter form, procedure for approval, drawing submission and approval flow, and so on;
* To attend the regular meeting, to check and confirm the work method, work performance, work progress, status of equipment and materials, work schedule and safety control as well as problems to be solved;
* To check the work plan, construction method, construction time schedule, construction equipment schedule, manning schedule and safety control plan proposed by the contractor;
* To check the quality control method for both construction site and laboratory (equipment and method) proposed by the contractor;
* To check and finalize the controlled point and bench marks for construction set by the contractor;
* To check the setting out lines and levels prepared by the contractor;
* To check the construction drawings, construction/ shop drawings, design, documents and calculations prepared and submitted by the contractor;
* To check the construction materials proposed by the contractor including proposed borrow areas;
* To supervise the laboratory testing and data preparation carried out by the contractor;
* To inspect the quarry sites, borrow areas, stock pile areas and factory supplying and/ or fabricating the materials for construction;
* To supervise the field test and the factory test and to determine the appropriate equipment and methods for quality control with project staff of government
* To inspect the construction method, equipment use, work performance and quality of site works comparing with the technical specification throughout the construction period with project staff of government;
* To survey and measure the work output performed by the contractor from a viewpoint of quality and progress;
* To control the total work quantities and cost in the Bill of Quantities (BoQ) contracted through the Mutual Check;
+ To inspect the safety control method and facilities applied by the contractor;

* To analyze and settle the contractor's claim in coordination with the Employer/ the Engineer;
* To check the as-built drawings prepared by the contractor;
* To keep proper records necessary for preparation of the completion report;
* To conduct final inspection of all completed works executed by the contractor with project staff of government and recommend to issue the completion certificate; and
* To check and certify the payment to contractors regularly;
* To prepare the completion report for respective parts including keeping proper records; and
* To prepare required technical report in the TOR.
**Candidate Specification:**
* Education: University graduate in irrigation or civil engineering
* Significant years working experience in planning, design, and construction supervision of irrigation, dam or other water resources development projects.

It would be preferable if the candidate also has the following specifications:
* Indonesian Project: At least 1 year work experience of professional A engineer in Indonesian irrigation project.
* Indonesian Language: Technical meeting level. (DGWR Irrigasi will have job interview).

